    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras are leaning into power and situational speed today, headlined by **Yordan Alvarez**, who claims the day\u2019s highest efficiency score of 77.33. His matchup against Andre Pallante is the primary engine here; despite a slight park penalty, his elite xwOBA and favorable platoon split position him as a must-start staple. Close behind, **Hyeseong Kim** (70.16) and **Colt Keith** (68.51) represent our strongest mid-tier pivots. **Hyeseong Kim** benefits immensely from a matchup against Ryan Feltner, where the combination of a favorable park and the pitcher\u2019s slow delivery creates an ideal environment to hunt for stolen bases\u2014a critical priority for our roster construction. Similarly, **Carson Benge** (67.06) is an aggressive play, leveraging an advantageous platoon split and a top-of-the-order boost that outweighs the volatility of facing Jameson Taillon.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Jerar Encarnacion**, whose score of 46.11 was the closest to cracking the utility spot. While his underlying metrics remain serviceable, he was ultimately edged out by the superior plate discipline and higher lineup security offered by **Junior Caminero**. The optimizer ultimately flagged the difficulty of **Junior Caminero**\u2019s matchup against Paul Skenes, yet the projected volume and order security still provided a higher probability of offensive output than the alternative. We are exercising caution with **Trea Turner** and **Kyle Schwarber**, as both face the significant hurdle of Chris Sale. While their base talent and favorable lineup spots keep them in the starting lineup, the elite skill level of Sale drags their individual scores into the 50s, requiring us to monitor the game closely for potential pinch-hit risks if they fail to produce early. All managers should note that these scores assume historical batting order placements; any late-breaking news dropping **Dillon Dingler** or **Victor Scott II** in the lineup will necessitate a re-evaluation of their projected efficiency.",
